<item>
            <title>[FLUME-1922] HDFS Sink should optionally insert the timestamp at the sink</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLUME-1922</link>
                <project id="12311321" key="FLUME">Flume</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The HDFS Sink currently looks for the timestamp in the event headers. If some events are delayed then the events will end up in the old directory itself. We should allow the HDFS Sink to use the local timestamp to decide where the event goes.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
